{"type":"text","timestamp":1778905123774,"sessionID":"ses_1d1028ea2ffevSTrimEHvR87Mj","part":{"id":"prt_e2f01ef2d001gcV0gRb6lftcoy","messageID":"msg_e2f01d4c1001sUng1dLZKNUaL1","sessionID":"ses_1d1028ea2ffevSTrimEHvR87Mj","type":"text","text":"I have addressed issue #3003. Here's what was done:\n\n1. **Read the issue context** — The definition of `UBERON:0002099` (cardiac septum) was too narrow, only covering septa between the atria or ventricles, while child terms also include outflow tract septa and atrioventricular septa.\n\n2. **Checked out the term** using `obo-checkout.pl` and reviewed all child terms (interatrial, interventricular, outflow tract, atrioventricular, and aortico-pulmonary spiral septa).\n\n3. **Updated the definition** from:\n   > \"The thin membranous structure between the two heart atria or the thick muscular structure between the two heart ventricles.\"\n   \n   to:\n   > \"A septum that is part of the heart and divides parts of the heart, including the atria, ventricles, and outflow tract.\"\n\n4. **Added a `term_tracker_item`** linking back to issue #3003.\n\n5. **Checked the term back in** and committed the change locally.\n\n6. **Created the required files:**\n   - `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md`\n   - `PR_COMMENTS.md`\n\nThe task is complete.","time":{"start":1778905116461,"end":1778905123772}}}
